aftenskifte Har du erfaring med reparation af kompositmaterialer og lyst til at udvikle dine kompetencer inden for kvalitet og træning. Tage et ansvar for andres læring og performance? Ønsker du at spille en nøglerolle i at sikre høj kvalitet i produktionen af vindmøllevinger? Vi søger en Kvalitetstræner, der kan træne og vejlede kvalitetsinspektører samt sikre en høj kvalitetsstandard i vores processer og produkter. Stillingen er ideel for dig, der har erfaring fra industrien – enten fra vingeproduktion, kompositreparationer eller en nuværende stilling i kvalitetsafdelingen, hvor du ønsker nye udfordringer i et nyt segment. Dine ansvarsområder: Træning, vejledning og certificering af kvalitetsinspektører, så de har den nødvendige viden om kvalitetskrav og processer inden for området Kvalitetssikring af produkter gennem implementering og forbedring af standarder Fejlfinding og problemhåndtering med fokus på reparationer af kompositmaterialer Dokumentation og rapportering, herunder arbejde med kvalitetsstyringssystemer (fx QSYS, PRISMA, Teamcenter) Dataanalyse og løbende forbedring af kvalitetssikringsprocesser og dokumentationspakke Samarbejde på tværs af afdelinger for at sikre alignment mellem kvalitets- og produktionsmål For at sikre en høj faglig standard bliver træneren certificeret hver 12. måned, og vores kvalitetsinspektører certificeres hver 6. måned. Hvem er du? Du har erfaring fra vindmølleindustrien – enten fra reparation af vinger, produktion eller kvalitetsarbejde Din faglige baggrund kan være af både praktisk og eller skolet karakter, eks. ingeniørbaggrund Du har kendskab til eller lyst til at dygtiggøre dig i reparationer af kompositmaterialer Du er serviceorienteret og evner at kommunikere professionelt med både interne og eksterne interessenter Du arbejder systematisk og har en god forståelse for kvalitetsstyring Du behersker engelsk i skrift og tale Det er en fordel, men ikke et krav, hvis du har erfaring med kvalitetsstyringssystemer (QSYS, PRISMA, Teamcenter) Vi tilbyder: En afvekslende hverdag med både træning af kvalitetsinspektører og praktisk kvalitetssikring Mulighed for at præge kvalitetsarbejdet og bidrage til kontinuerlige forbedringer Tæt samarbejde med procesejere, Customer Quality Engineers og tilsvarende kollega på dag-skifte Personlig og faglig udvikling i en virksomhed, der arbejder med grøn energi En international arbejdsplads, hvor kvalitet og innovation er i fokus Arbejdstid: Mandag-torsdag, kl. 18-03 Er du klar til at tage ansvar for kvalitetstræning og udvikling? Ansøg via Workday ved at bruge \"Ansøg nu / Apply now\"-knappen nedenfor. Har du spørgsmål til stillingen og er nysgerrig? Ved spørgsmål til jobbet kantakt Jørgen Barrit – 30 37 74 78 Ved spørgsmål til rekrutering, kontakt Daniela Johnsen på Daniela.johnsen.ext@siemensgamesa.com, bemærk venligst at CV og ansøgninger modtages kun via Workday. Siemens Gamesa is an equal opportunity employer and maintains a work environment that is free from discrimination and where employees are treated with dignity and respect. Employment at Siemens Gamesa is based solely on an individual''s merit and qualifications, which are directly related to job competence. Siemens Gamesa does not discriminate against any employee or job applicant on the basis of race, ethnicity, nationality, ancestry, genetic information, citizenship, religion, age, gender, gender identity/expression, sexual orientation, pregnancy, marital status, disability or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, rules or regulations. We adhere to these principles in all aspects of employment, including recruiting, hiring, training, compensation, promotion and benefits. We are driven by people - from more than 100 different countries, they build the company we are every day. Our diverse and inclusive culture encourages us to think outside the box, speak without fear, and be bold. We value the flexibility that our smart-working arrangements, our digital disconnection framework and our family-friendly practices bring to the new way of working. With a worldwide installed capacity of 139 GW, Siemens Gamesa Renewable Energy has a presence in more than 100 countries and a team of 30,000 people worldwide. Its end-to-end value chain presence encompasses onshore and offshores wind turbines design, manufacturing, installation as well as cutting-edge service solutions. Siemens Gamesa Renewable Energy is part of Siemens Energy, a global leader in energy technology with a rich legacy of innovation spanning over 150 years.","job_location":"Danmark","job_employment_type":"Fuld tid"}]}', 'udvikler');
INSERT INTO public.job_search_result (id, json_response, query) VALUES (4, '{"status":"OK","request_id":"b734f869-0e59-4de1-b0e4-8cc836f57969","parameters":{"query":"backend udvikler københavn","page":1,"num_pages":1,"country":"dk","language":"en","date_posted":"all","job_requirements":null,"radius":500},"data":[{"job_id":"k-93JqrXVCTJTBRrAAAAAA==","job_title":"Typescript Backend Developer","employer_name":"Shape – Becoming Framna","job_description":"🌟 BECOME A PART OF THE TEAM\n\nFramna, which means ‘to advance'' or ‘to bring forward'' in Old Norse, was born from the union of Shape, Bontouch, and Move. At Framna, we create digital products that over 10 million people worldwide depend on every day. Our products boast an average App Store rating of 4.5, and we process over €150 million daily through our digital solutions. Collaborating closely with some of the world''s most ambitious brands – including IKEA, H&M, PostNord, SEB, Swish, OK, B&O, Systembolaget, Post-it, Progressive, Novo Nordisk, Essity, Rabobank, ENGIE, and many others – we strive to make them leaders in their respective industry categories by delivering high-quality, award-winning digital products.\n\nFramna has emerged from the strong product-led culture of Shape, Bontouch, and Move joining forces. Our 500+ colleagues work across eight studios located in Sweden, Denmark, the USA, Switzerland, and the Netherlands.\n\nAS OUR BACKEND DEVELOPER, YOU WILL...\n• Become a key member of team consisting of 2 - 10 developers specialized in backend, Android, and iOS development who are responsible for building and maintaining 1 - 3 existing or new projects.\n• Be part of a company that prioritize work-life balance and recognize that employees perform at their best when their personal life is supported and stable.\n• Participate in creating scalable, maintainable, and tested software that we can work with over the next several years.\n• Work in close collaboration with our design, quality assurance, and strategic teams to build delightful products that make a difference in people’s lives.\n• Deploy and monitor the developed solutions to ensure high availability and low error rates. We typically use containerized environments on AWS or Azure.\n• Get the opportunity to share your knowledge with your fellow colleagues as well as learn from them during day-to-day work and our scheduled knowledge-sharing sessions.\n• Operate in an open, inspiring, and highly trust-based environment, where your opinion matters a lot and will highly define the direction of our codebases as well as the experience we deliver to our users.\n• Be assigned a mentor, regardless of your experience level, for the first weeks at work, just so you can get familiar with the Shape ways of working (and coding).\n\nSOME OF THE THINGS WE LOOK FOR...\n• Experience building APIs using Typescript.\n• Motivation to become a part of and learn from a team of experienced and passionate developers for backend, web, iOS and Android.\n• An interest in system architecture, caching techniques, REST API design and data modeling.\n• Experience working with relational databases such as Postgres and Elastic Search.\n• Experience with Docker and at least one public cloud (AWS, Azure, GCP). Having worked with techniques and technologies such as Infrastructure as Code, Load Balancing, Redis, and managed services such as S3 is a plus.\n• Experience with running and monitoring applications in production.\n• Nice to have: experience with Scala (alternatively Java or Kotlin), Spark, Python.\n\nWORKING HOURS AND SPECIFICATIONS\n\n⏱ Full-time, 37.5 hours a week.\n\n📍 This is a Copenhagen-based, on-site position with flexible remote work possibilities.\n\n💬 English proficiency is a must. Danish language skills are not expected.\n\n💎 Read more about our benefits and why to choose Shape on our career page.\n\nHIRING PROCESS\n\n📝 Application via the company career site\n\n🕵🏻 CV screening by a Talent Acquisition team\n\n👥 1st meeting with a Talent Acquisition team\n\n🧑💻 Take-home assignment - a small application to work on from scratch\n\n💁 2nd meeting - technical interview with a panel of senior developers\n\n👨👩👧👦 3rd meeting - Team and cultural fit [helpful for both candidate and team to get acquainted before deciding \"it''s a match\"!]\n\n🎯 Offer\n\nPERKS AND BENEFITS\n\n🏙 Central office\n\nOur office is located in a central area of Copenhagen, Denmark. Easy to access by bike or public transport (metro station: Islands Brygge).\n\n🍝☕️ Food and drinks\n\nEnjoy a catered lunch, great snacks, and drinks with your colleagues, every day. These include plenty of vegetarian, halal, gluten, and lactose-free options.\n\n🧑🎓 Skill development\n\nWe support your skill development by offering a budget to attend conferences.\n\n👯 Social gatherings\n\nEnjoy social gatherings, activities, Friday bars, and games together with your colleagues.\n\n⚖️ Work-life balance\n\nWork is not everything. Carve out time for your family, friends, and fun hobbies.\n\n🐥 Family friendly\n\nWe cherish families and understand that daily life can be full of unexpected events. We also open our doors to your little ones for Christmas Hygge or LEGO nights.\n\n🏡 Remote work allowed\n\nWe are open to remote work as long as it fits in with your team. Working from your home country is also possible when visiting your family and friends.\n\nWORKING WITH US\n\n⭐️ We are organized with a very flat hierarchy without unnecessary project managers, but with team leads who also have technical backgrounds.\n\n⭐️ Our office is located in Islands Brygge close to public transportation and the harbor, where both summertime and wintertime swimming is enjoyed.\n\n⭐️ The headquarters offers a modern aesthetic, a comfy lounge area, and plenty of fun activities such as PlayStation tournaments, board game nights, family LEGO days, robot wars, and much more.\n\n⭐️ But also social events, keynotes, morning runs (and swims) and Friday bars - not to forget an unhealthy amount of snacks, beverages, cake.\n\n⭐️ Our team is very international and so far includes people from over 30 different countries. Our company language is English.\n\n⭐️ Read more about our benefits and why to choose us on our career page.","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"PNMZckyvRpFk_yI-AAAAAA==","job_title":"Backend-udvikler","employer_name":"Emento A/S","job_description":"Sådan her ville det normale jobopslag nok starte: Vil du arbejde i en fremadstormende scale up inden for Healthcare IT, og drømmer du om at få (måske) Danmarks bedste kollegaer? Har du erfaring som backend-udvikler? Så er det dig vi mangler i Emento!\n\n... men hos os gør vi nogle gange tingene lidt anderledes.\n\nDerfor har vores dev team skrevet, indspillet og filmet denne sang til dig - for at vise hvor meget vores frontendere har brug for dig, som vores nye backender. Men også hvor meget vi glæder os til at møde dig! Videoen giver dig desuden et lille indblik i hvem dev teamet består af - for alle 10 udviklere er med, ud af i alt ca. 25 ansatte i Emento.\n\nOg nå ja, så havde vi det også ret sjovt med at indspille sangen\n\nUd over dit indtryk af os fra musikvideoen, hvem er vi så? Her kommer lige et par hurtige facts:\n• Vi snakker meget sammen! Både fordi vi har meget på hjerte, men også fordi vi går meget op i at hjælpe hinanden. Omvendt kender vi også værdien af at fordybe sig i en opgave\n• Vi tror hårdnakket på, at man udvikler bedre software, hvis man først og fremmest har det godt.\n• Selv om det lyder meget floskel agtigt, så synes vi det er fantastisk motiverende at vores produkt gør en forskel i mange mennesker liv og skaber så stor værdi\n• Siden 2022 har vi haft en afdeling i Tyskland, hvor der er en masse spændende muligheder for at guide patienter med digitale værktøjer\n• Der er desværre en lidt skæv kønsfordeling på dev teamet, men det opvejes heldigvis af resten af Emento\n• Vi går ret meget op i tillid - så meget, at Dansk Design Center på et tidspunkt udråbte os til digitale etik-helte på deres SoMe-kanaler\n\nTeknologier vi arbejder med er: Javascript, Node.JS, MongoDB, Docker, Ansible, Microservices, REST, Nginx, Linux\n\nHvem er du så?\n\nNu har vi jo ikke mødt dig endnu, men vi forestiller os du er sådan en der kan li'' f.eks:\n• Opbygning og vedligehold af driftsmiljøer\n• Udvikling af API''er og integrationer\n• Informationssikerhed og GDPR\n• Kryptering og sikring af data\n• Opsætning og implementering af integrations- og beskedbus\n• BI data\n• Machine Learning\n\nVi leder efter en der har:\n• Erfaring med udvikling af backend-systemer\n• Erfaring med dokument-baserede databaser\n• Ingen krav om specifik teknologi\n• Lyst til at lære nyt\n\nPS. Det er altså ikke et krav at du kan spille musik Og det er heller ikke et must at du ved hvilket instrument, den blå dims Chris spiller på ved 01:43 er - men det giver da klart plus point\n\nVi vil meget gerne starte med en uformel samtale over en kop kaffe eller en cola, så hermed en åben invitation til at invitere dig selv på kaffe - skriv til Mikkel på mikkel@emento.dk eller via LinkedIn og hvis du foretrækker at ringe, så træf Chris på 5188 0913\n\nHvad er Emento i øvrigt for en størrelse?\n\nEmento blev stiftet i 2016 og har i dag ca. 45 ansatte. Emento har base i Aarhus N (Olof Palmes Allé 44, 8200), samt kontor i Kødbyen i København og i Düsseldorf, Tyskland. Vi har kunder indenfor både hospitaler og kommuner i hele Danmark og Tyskalnd. Vi bygger vores produktsuite baseret på Design Thinking / Service Design, fordi vi tror på at samskabelse i udviklingsprocesser, faktisk gør en reel forskel for vores brugere.","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"uh9lSKQ-Oe0viZ4aAAAAAA==","job_title":"Backend udvikler søges til innovativ og værdiskabende virksomhed","employer_name":"STELLA CARE ApS","job_description":"Har du erfaring med backend udvikling i .NET/C#? Kunne du tænke dig at indgå i et udviklerteam på fire, og få vigtig indflydelse i virksomhedens vækst? Betyder det noget for dig, at dit arbejde er værdiskabende, og du hver dag gør en væsentlig forskel i mange menneskers liv? Vil du være en del af et stærkt udviklerteam, som designer og udvikler effektive systemer og løsninger? Så læs endelig videre.\n\nHvem er vi?\nVi designer og udvikler systemer, som skaber tryghed for mennesker med demens, plejepersonale og pårørende. Dette gør vi med GPS-lokalisering, primært gennem udvikling af software til Samsung smart-ure, backend, frontend-administrationssystem samt apps til iOS og Android.\n\nStella Care er en innovativ iværksættervirksomhed, som er markedsledende i Danmark, og det er vi stolte af. En position vi har skabt ved at arbejde passioneret og resultatorienteret på ved at skabe løsninger med fokus på intuitiv brugervenlighed og kvalitet.\n\nVi er i udvikling og har travlt. Vi har nu startet migreringen af vores mange kunder til en ny platform. Det vil sige til ny backend, frontend og nye apps. Derudover laver vi integration til kommunernes AD-systemer, så kommunerne selv kan styre rettigheds- og adgangsforhold. Desuden arbejder vi utrætteligt på optimeringer og forbedringer i vores GPS-ure samt på nye features og funktioner.\n\nKulturen i Stella Care er inkluderende, åben og ansvarlig. Vi foretrækker den åbne og frie dialog, da den fremmer vores samarbejde, trivsel og passion.\n\nMålet er nye, kundevendte funktioner via vores administrationssystem, så vores kunder i højere grad selv kan finde alle oplysninger og de kan betjene sig selv med hensyn til opsætning af GPS-enheder, brugerlogins, bestillinger og ombytninger. Alt sammen i intuitivt design. Derudover arbejder vi hele tiden på optimeringer i GPS-urene, der kan forbedre funktion, brugervenlighed og batteritid.\n\nDine arbejdsopgaver\nArbejdsopgaverne er meget varierende, men vil primært være på backend relaterede opgaver hvor du skal være med til:\nSpecificering, design, implementering og idriftsættelse af nye funktioner. Fx har vi netop implementeret login med MitID. Udarbejdelse og sikring af skalerbare løsninger – fra API, Database og Micro Services.\n\nDine egenskaber og kvalifikationer\nDu har erfaring med .Net og du arbejder både på overordnet niveau og du kan dykke ned i detaljen. Du er struktureret, analytisk og har øje for detaljer. Du er pragmatiker. Du afslutter opgaver indenfor den deadline du har sat.\n\nDu er fortrolig med\n• .Net Core\n• MySQL/SQL\n• Entity Framework\n• Test og kvalitetssikring\n• Kubernetes\n\nArbejdssted\nVi har til huse i skønne lokaler på Kalkbrænderiløbskaj 6A i København Ø i et inspirerende miljø i et charmerende pakhus, der ligger ned til vandet.\n\nStella Care tilbyder\n• En garanti for, at det du gør, er værdiskabende. Sammen gør vi en væsentlig forskel for rigtig mange mennesker – hver dag vi går på arbejde\n• Du får et meningsfuldt ansvar med vigtig indflydelse og ikke mindst fleksibilitet\n• Udviklingsmuligheder både fagligt som personligt\n• En virksomhed med entreprenørånd og passion\n• God kantineordning – Meyers\n• Sundhedsforsikring og pension\n\nEr du nysgerrig, så kig på vores hjemmeside og læs mere om, hvordan vi gør en forskel samt se vores produktsortiment.\n\nAnsøgning\nSendes til e-mail\nYderligere oplysninger får du hos CTO Søren Christiansen på telefon 42429070 eller CEO Rasmus Hansen på telefon 42429050.\nTiltrædelse er snarest muligt og der afholdes samtaler løbende.\n\nOm Stella Care\nStella Care startede i 2012, og vi er en service- og teknologivirksomhed med en mission om, at hjælpe mennesker med demens. Vores mål er, at ingen demensramte forsvinder sporløst. Stella Cares løsning benyttes i dag af mere end 60 kommuner i Danmark, og vores løsninger er på vej ind i resten af Skandinavien.","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"G-IR97_bw-zjZXC-AAAAAA==","job_title":"Backend Developer","employer_name":"Corti","job_description":"There is no quality healthcare without a quality dialogue. Today, that dialogue is broken; we need you to help us fix it.\n\nDoctors and nurses across the world are facing unprecedented challenges. When we meet them, they''re dealing with heavy workloads, extensive paperwork, and the pressure of performing well, which in healthcare, can have dire consequences. This system is gradually undermining the passion and autonomy of our dedicated healthcare professionals, who entered this field to provide care, not to clerk.\n\nCorti has built the world''s premier AI assistant for healthcare providers. It listens in during patient dialogue, takes notes, writes summaries, journals and does quality assurance. When information is missed, or risk is high, it offers nudges and prompts to help steer the dialogue back on the right path. Entire countries trust Corti to deliver better healthcare, and our AI has already helped millions of patients, but we are just getting started.\n\nAre you a curious person, and interested in contributing to solving real problems in healthcare? Are you someone who loves the Golang programming language? At Corti, we are growing fast and are looking for fresh talent to make sure we go in the right direction! If you enjoy working in a fun, autonomous, and collaborative team, guided by shared values, and a willingness to act, iterate, and learn…\n\n…then join us at Corti as Backend Engineer in the Engineering team.\n\nJoin the team as a Backend Engineer to be part of pioneering the development of healthcare products. Our team specifically focuses on developing software that assists the medical community. Your work will build the backend that helps the medics, nurses, and doctors learn from their calls to get better for each one. You will learn every day by working alongside experts in software engineering, machine learning, and data science—are you up for the adventure?\n\nThe impact you''ll have:\n• Own the technical development of a product that differentiates Corti the most in the market\n• Your development work will impact millions of medical consultations a year at a global scale\n• Hands-on development of an innovative solution where design choices matter\n• Collaborate across our product and platform teams to define and improve best practices across Corti\n• Work with colleagues in design and code reviews\n• Bridge technical communication between end-users, technical leads, and Corti engineers\n• Contribute to a strong culture of development at Corti\n\nTo thrive in this role, you''ll need:\n• Minimum 2 years of experience as a backend developer\n• Experience in Golang\n• Experience ideating and implementing features with high complexity\n• Hands-on experience with cloud computing architecture and development\n• Deep experience with software and product development processes - you have seen where problems can arise, know how to deal with them, and how they can be proactively avoided\n• Experience running, monitoring, and operating REST, WebSockets, and GraphQL APIs\n• You know what it takes to make APIs more public & accessible\n• Experience with containers and orchestration tools\n• A passion for writing clean and efficient code\n\nBonus experience:\n• Understand what it takes to build integration with other systems used in healthcare\n• Experience designing data storage solutions\n\nBenefits:\n• Ability to work in a hybrid model in our office in central Copenhagen\n• Trips to somewhere nice , for team camps (both company-wide and team-specific ones) - We went to Portugal last year!\n• Investment in learning & developing you and your career\n• Paid parental leave, company pension scheme and health insurance\n• We support your family and take care of you when you are old!\n• Catered lunch in our office in Copenhagen\n\nReady to dive into the world of Corti? Hit that ''Apply'' button, and let''s start working together on reshaping the dialogue in healthcare, making a real difference for millions of patient outcomes around the world.\n\nBringing in top talent from all backgrounds is crucial in our pursuit to improve the world of healthcare. We encourage applications from all people and do not discriminate based on race, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, and/or disability status.﻿\n\nAt Corti, experience comes in many forms, and we’re passionate about creating teams with a multitude of perspectives! If you believe your experience is close to what we’re looking for but not an exact match, we still hope you’ll consider applying!","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"Ei6w8ZvP2NUXaQmmAAAAAA==","job_title":"Backend .NET Developer","employer_name":"Novicell Denmark","job_description":"At Novicell, we are looking for a backend .NET Developer to join our team!\nAbout the job\n\nYou will be part of the development team in our Copenhagen department, working closely with 30+ skilled and ambitious employees, including front-end and back-end developers, QA specialists, solutions architects, designers, and project managers.\n\nYou will collaborate closely with a team of back-end and front-end developers to help solve business problems for our clients.\n\nYour responsibilities will include developing back-end solutions using .NET, working on tasks such as integration layers, custom applications, and the setup of Azure infrastructure.\n\nIn conjunction with architects, designers and strategists, you will advise clients on making decisions about software and infrastructure based on their specific requirements. In Copenhagen we emphasize working in blended teams and learning from perspectives of other practices.\n\nYou will develop solutions that require integration across a variety of systems, such as CMS, CRM, PIM, DAM, ERP, and many more.\n\nWe build on the MACH-architecture, which means that:\n• Microservices – Our APIs consist of micro-service runtimes that communicate, and our integration layers are built on Azure Functions.\n• API-FIRST – Our solutions are API-driven, allowing front-end developers to deliver the best possible UX experience on top of the underlying APIs.\n• Cloud Native – We use the latest cloud services such as message queues, API gateways, and Function Apps in Azure.\n• Headless – Underlying CMSs are used in headless format and the presentation is not dictated by the CMS.\n\nAbout Novicell\n\nNovicell is a premier digital consulting firm dedicated to helping companies unlock their digital potential. By blending technical expertise with creative innovation, we deliver bespoke solutions tailored to our clients’ needs. Our diverse team of specialists collaborates with a singular focus: achieving exceptional results and pushing the boundaries of digital development.\n\nOur motto, “Kind & Diligent,” embodies our core values of integrity and collaboration. Rather than relying on traditional, lengthy employee handbooks and rules, we cultivate a culture of open dialogue and shared responsibility. We believe that a joyful work environment is crucial for employee satisfaction, motivation, creativity, and strong team relationships. At Novicell, we strive to make fun and joy an integral part of every workday. Hence, at Novicell, you will experience:\n• An informal organization with significant personal freedom.\n• A creative and inspiring environment where you can shape the company''s ongoing development.\n• A dedicated focus on personal and professional development.\n• A strong social culture with many activities and events.\n• The kindest and most diligent colleagues in the industry!\n\nRole and responsibilities\n\nAs a back-end .NET Developer at Novicell Copenhagen, you will:\n• Refine complex business requirements for our clients, breaking them down into manageable tasks that can be estimated and planned into sprints.\n• Advise clients on optimal solutions that perfectly align with their business needs, ensuring a balanced approach to scope, budget, and timeline.\n• Collaborate closely with cloud specialists to establish secure, future-proof hosting infrastructure with the necessary performance and scalability.\n• Work in tandem with front-end developers to discuss data and requirements, ensuring the creation of well-documented APIs.\n• Develop seamless integrations between various systems.\n• Partner with QA specialists to ensure a shared understanding and thorough testing of complex business logic.\n• Leverage CMS experience to build and configure CMS solutions for our clients, if applicable.\n\nAbout you\n\nTo succeed in this role, we expect that you\n• Have several years of experience building .NET solutions.\n• Have experience working with the latest .NET technologies.\n• Have experience in developing integrations and APIs.\n• Have experience working in a consultancy environment or engaging in dialogue with stakeholders. Ideally, you can understand business requirements and break them down into tasks.\n• Have experience with Azure Services, such as app services, functions, storage accounts, service bus, API gateways, etc.\n• Have experience with Azure DevOps, including build and release pipelines.\n• Have experience with CMS systems such as Umbraco, DynamicWeb, or similar.\n• Are self-driven, proactive, take responsibility, and follow through on tasks.\n• Can contribute knowledge to the team and across departments.\n\nHow to apply\n\nYou are welcome to submit your application and CV in English or Danish. This will have no impact on our assessment of your profile or skills.\n\nWe process applications continuously and will close the job opening once the right candidate has been found.\n\nRead more about Novicell here","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"UpYU_AULvLCHCEfjAAAAAA==","job_title":"Backend Developer","employer_name":"Shape","job_description":"BECOME A PART OF THE TEAM\n\nFramna, which means ‘to advance'' or ‘to bring forward'' in Old Norse, was born from the union of Shape, Bontouch, and Move. At Framna, we create digital products that over 10 million people worldwide depend on every day. Our products boast an average App Store rating of 4.5, and we process over €150 million daily through our digital solutions. Collaborating closely with some of the world''s most ambitious brands – including IKEA, H&M, PostNord, SEB, Swish, OK, B&O, Systembolaget, Post-it, Progressive, Novo Nordisk, Essity, Rabobank, ENGIE, and many others – we strive to make them leaders in their respective industry categories by delivering high-quality, award-winning digital products.\n\nFramna has emerged from the strong product-led culture of Shape, Bontouch, and Move joining forces. Our 550+ colleagues work across eight studios located in Sweden, Denmark, the USA, Switzerland, and the Netherlands.\n\nSOME OF THE THINGS WE LOOK FOR...\n• Experience with modern web frameworks such as Spring, Ktor, Rails or similar.\n• Motivation to become a part of and learn from a team of experienced and passionate developers for backend, web, iOS and Android.\n• Experience with Kotlin or Java.\n• An interest in system architecture, caching techniques, REST API design and data modeling.\n• Experience working with relational databases such as Postgres.\n• Experience with Docker and at least one public cloud (AWS, Azure, GCP). Having worked with techniques and technologies such as Infrastructure as Code, Load Balancing, Redis, and managed services such as S3 is a plus.\n• Experience with running and monitoring applications in production.\n• It’s always good to also know frontend technologies such as React or Vue.\n\nAS OUR BACKEND DEVELOPER, YOU WILL...\n• Become a key member of team consisting of 2 - 10 developers specialized in backend, Android, and iOS development who are responsible for building and maintaining 1 - 3 existing or new projects.\n• Be part of a company that prioritize work-life balance and recognize that employees perform at their best when their personal life is supported and stable.\n• Participate in creating scalable, maintainable, and tested software that we can work with over the next several years.\n• Work in close collaboration with our design, quality assurance, and strategic teams to build delightful products that make a difference in people’s lives.\n• Deploy and monitor the developed solutions to ensure high availability and low error rates. We typically use containerized environments on AWS or Azure.\n• Get the opportunity to share your knowledge with your fellow colleagues as well as learn from them during day-to-day work and our scheduled knowledge-sharing sessions.\n• Operate in an open, inspiring, and highly trust-based environment, where your opinion matters a lot and will highly define the direction of our codebases as well as the experience we deliver to our users.\n• Be assigned a mentor, regardless of your experience level, for the first weeks at work, just so you can get familiar with the Shape ways of working (and coding).\n\nHIRING PROCESS\n\n📝 Application via the company career site\n\n🕵🏻 CV screening by Talent Acquisition team\n\n👥 1st meeting with Talent Acquisition team\n\n🧑‍💻 Take-home assignment - a small application to work on from scratch\n\n💁 2nd meeting - technical interview with a panel of senior developers\n\n👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 3rd meeting - Team and cultural fit [helpful for both you and team to get acquainted before deciding that \"it''s a match\"!]\n\n🎯 Offer\n\nPERKS AND BENEFITS\n\n🏙 Central office\n\nOur office is located in a central area of Copenhagen, Denmark. Easy to access by bike or public transport (metro station: Islands Brygge).\n\n🍝☕️ Food and drinks\n\nEnjoy a catered lunch, great snacks, and drinks with your colleagues, every day. These include plenty of vegetarian, halal, gluten, and lactose-free options.\n\n🧑‍🎓 Skill development\n\nWe support your skill development by offering a budget to attend conferences.\n\n👯 Social gatherings\n\nEnjoy social gatherings, activities, Friday bars, and games together with your colleagues.\n\n⚖️ Work-life balance\n\nWork is not everything. Carve out time for your family, friends, and fun hobbies.\n\n🐥 Family friendly\n\nWe cherish families and understand that daily life can be full of unexpected events. We also open our doors to your little ones for Christmas Hygge or LEGO nights.\n\nWORKING WITH US\n\n⭐️ A competitive salary in accordance with experience and capabilities.\n\n⭐️ We are organized with a very flat hierarchy without unnecessary project managers, but with team leads who also have technical backgrounds.\n\n⭐️ Our office is located in Islands Brygge close to public transportation and the harbor, where both summertime and wintertime swimming is enjoyed.\n\n⭐️ The headquarters offers a modern aesthetic, a comfy lounge area, and plenty of fun activities such as PlayStation tournaments, board game nights, family LEGO days, robot wars, and much more.\n\n⭐️ But also social events, keynotes, morning runs (and swims) and Friday bars - not to forget an unhealthy amount of snacks, beverages, cake.\n\n⭐️ Our team is very international and so far includes people from over 30 different countries. Our company language is English.\n\n⭐️ Read more about our benefits and why to choose us on our career page.","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"f8rzuRMDLe2RZfqlAAAAAA==","job_title":"Senior Software Engineer - Backend (Java/Spring boot)","employer_name":"Too Good To Go","job_description":"At Too Good To Go, we have an ambitious goal: to inspire and empower everyone to fight food waste together.\n\n40% of all food produced in the world is wasted. And that has a huge impact on the health of our planet, with 10% of greenhouse gas emissions coming from food waste.\n\nWe’re more than an app: we are a certified B Corporation with a mission to empower everyone to take action against food waste, so alongside our marketplace app, we create educational tools, explore new business solutions - such as our Retail Technologies offering, and influence legislation to help reduce food waste.\n\nWe’re growing fast: Our community of 115 million registered users and 241,000 active partners across 19 countries, have together already prevented 428+ million meals from going to waste - avoiding over 1.157.000 tonnes of CO2e!\n\nThe Roles\n\nWe are looking to recruit Senior Backend Software Engineers, to be a part of our Product Teams that defines, builds, and delivers our product features. As a Senior Team Member in a product team, you will work towards specific outcomes with the freedom and responsibility to figure out the best way to achieve them together with the other Engineers and other Product Team members.\n\nYour role encompasses refining, architecting, executing, and actively contributing to the continuous evolution of our team''s capabilities.\n\nAs a Senior, you will actively support your engineering lead in delivering a quality, maintainable and international top-class product, whilst being a role model for less-senior team members, by taking responsibility for problems and using your expertise to identify the right solutions.\n\nThe Tech Stack\n\nWe have created a scalable Spring Boot Application running on Java 21 in Kubernetes, deployed in a multi-region setup in AWS. Developers are able to run a full development environment locally, which gives a great developer experience.\n\nYour Mission\n• Build and evolve our backend services and infrastructure to stay ahead of our growth curve.\n• Develop exciting new features to make our users and partners’ experience better\n• Actively participate in your team’s development processes with a continuous improvement mindset.\n• Strive to deliver international top-class products with maximum quality, maintainability and scalability.\n• Take on additional tasks outside your current boundaries with help from your team to continue to grow and expand your skills.\n\nThe ideal candidates\n• Have a wealth of experience in Backend development within the Java ecosystem.\n• Have proven production experience with Java, Spring Boot, MySQL & Message Systems.\n• Have worked with Domain Driven Design, and Clean or Hexagonal Architecture.\n• Have deep knowledge of AWS services (SQS, SNS, S3…).\n• Have experience with building scalable solutions.\n• Enjoy actively participating in a cross-functional product team.\n• Take pride in writing quality code.\n\nOur values\n• We win together: Food waste is a big beast to fight. We believe in a #oneteam.\n• We raise the bar: We always push for more. We work smart, smash barriers and elevate one another.\n• We keep it simple: Our ambitions are bold but our solutions are simple.\n• We build a legacy: We’re proud of the change we’re driving.\n• We care: We always look out for each other. Caring is also about the way we do business. We do the right thing.\n\nWhat We Have To Offer\n• An opportunity to work in a global social-impact company and certified B Corporation! where you can see a real and tangible impact in your role.\n• To be an integral member of our defined product teams. We are eager for you to make an impact and contribute to the product scope and development; Your insights are valuable, and we are here to listen.\n• Work-life balance is important to us! Focus on the job to be done, not the hours spent, there is no need for overtime. On-call duty is not part of the job, but can be additionally agreed upon should you and your manager both wish it. We believe that happy environments create happy employees.\n• We trust in our employees and encourage an autonomous environment that provides several opportunities for employees to contribute, develop and take ownership of their work in a way that works for them.\n• To be part of an international company, with over 1,300+ colleagues across 19 countries that are on the same important mission.\n• An informal environment, working alongside 180+ passionate people within Tech & Product\n• We celebrate our differences and our successes and have a strong values-driven team culture.\n• We work in a hybrid set-up and value in office work weekly.\n• We may be able to support you with a working visa in Copenhagen, please be prepared to discuss this topic further as your first stage interview.\n\nHow to apply\n• We take recruitment very seriously, so please carefully read everything we have written above. Please also check our website and international media in order to get a good overview of Too Good To Go.\n• Submit your CV and Cover letter in English.\n• Please note that we only accept applications coming through our platform. No CV or Cover Letter will be accepted by email or LinkedIn direct messaging.\n\nJob Ref: #LI-TC1\n\n#LI-Hybrid\n\nA Movement for Everyone\nWe want to inspire and empower everyone to fight food waste together. With that mission, it’s only natural that we want to build a diverse and inclusive team of highly capable individuals who are passionate about doing things in a better way. We strongly believe we all excel and are more creative when we’re allowed to be ourselves, and we’re committed to a culture where all of us belong.\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and all employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. If you need reasonable accommodation at any point in the application or interview process, please let us know.","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"FuJytOWd8Cxdewy5AAAAAA==","job_title":"Senior Backend Engineer (ML)","employer_name":"Fullview","job_description":"Job Title: Senior Backend Engineer (ML)\n\nExperience: Senior/Staff\n\nCompany: Fullview\n\nLocation: Copenhagen-DK or Remote (no outsourcing)\n\nAbout Fullview\n\nFullview is a rapidly growing venture-backed startup, founded in 2022, dedicated to empowering companies to provide exceptional customer support experiences at scale. With strong support from investors behind successful companies like Pleo, Revolut, Stripe, Wiz, Grafana, Mistral AI and more, we are poised for continuous growth and innovation to help companies deliver faster customer support .\n\nWith Fullview''s cobrowsing solution, customer support teams from companies like Michelin, First National Bank and Personio, can see and visually guide their customers inside their web and mobile products, delivering a faster and better support experience.\n\nIn engineering, we are currently working on a number of ambitious initiatives that are going to take the customer support space to a new level, particularly delivering customers on-screen guidance, step-by-step, fully automated. Our awesome team of 10 engineers, spread across EU, needs help from experienced engineers who are excited about the AI-revolution, find it fascinating to build a product that is being leveraged to support millions of users, value ownership, and are geared towards action with intensity.\n\nWhat You''re Going To Do\n• Help us further develop and maintain our global SaaS product, leveraging technologies such as .NET 9, Orleans, NodeJS, MongoDb, ElasticSearch, K8s, Redpanda, NGINX and Terraform, among others\n• Drive our initiatives, leveraging modern AI for automated customer support, dealing with all aspects of bringing such a solution to life like data-extraction/-preparation, contextualization, CoT, RAG, evaluating top-notch tech for executing on our product vision\n• Evaluate options and tools to achieve our goals more efficiently, if applicable by driving PoCs and RFCs shared with the team\n• Collaborate closely with the engineering team and founders while also engaging directly with customers through Slack channels, emails or occasional meetings\n\nWhat We''re Looking For\n• A minimum of 5+ years of professional software development experience on large-scale distributed systems\n• Proficient in at least one of these stacks: .NET (>5), Go, Java\n• You enjoy digging into the details of service implementations and continuously help to improve them as the platform grows\n• Passion for performance-tuning and efficient resource-consumption\n• Code quality and system security aren’t an afterthought for you, and you achieve this through automation, unit testing, and structured code reviews\n• You make clear communication a priority and do not refrain from openly discussing thoughts and opinions with a clear focus on solving issues at hand in a pragmatic way\n• Bonus points: previous experience at a fast-growing startup that dealt with high-traffic and scaling challenges\n\nWhat We Offer\n• 💰Competitive salary, equity, and performance bonuses\n• 🧑💻 Hybrid work structure with flexible work hours\n• 🤝 Work directly with founders in a flat hierarchy\n• 🔥 VC-backed fast-growing company\n• ⛵️ Office at Blox with a great view of the harbour, all the amenities you need\n• 🏝️ Bi-annually team offsites","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"B_ZDdlHHOb4Ixz_RAAAAAA==","job_title":"Senior Software Developer (Backend) (m/f/d)","employer_name":"Chaos","job_description":"• *This position is based in Copenhagen, Denmark (hybrid). Applicants must hold a valid work/residence permit for the respective location.**\n\nChaos is the world’s largest 3D visualization software company, and for over 20 years has empowered artists, designers, and architects to visualize anything they can imagine. Chaos offers intuitive and powerful workflows for creatives across the entire design spectrum, including architecture, engineering, construction, product design, manufacturing, and media and entertainment. Research and development at Chaos is leading the way towards a truly comprehensive end-to-end visualization ecosystem to meet the evolving needs of existing and new customers. In 2022, Chaos merged with Enscape and acquired Cylindo. For more information, visit chaos.com, enscape3d.com, and cylindo.com.\n\nThe impact you will have in this role:\n\nChaos Cylindo is a cutting-edge 3D product visualization platform for commerce that makes creating, managing, and distributing photorealistic product visuals easy, from creating digital clones of customer products to managing the V-Ray-based production pipeline and distributing content to our customers’ e-commerce platforms.\n\nAs a Senior Software Developer at Chaos Cylindo, you will join our cross-functional Content Creation team. This team is responsible for our 3D production pipeline and tooling to utilize the created 3D assets, like our web-based 3D editor and AI lifestyle image generation tool.\n\nAt Chaos Cylindo, we innovate at scale and prioritize rapid development, all while putting our customers first. Despite our size, we operate with the agility of a start-up, so being able to juggle multiple projects is crucial.\n\nIn this role, you will:\n• Collaborate with design and product teams, from brainstorming to deployment, creating seamless product experiences.\n• Write clean, efficient, and maintainable code as part of an agile development team.\n• Participate in architecture discussions and help steer the technical direction of new features.\n• Troubleshoot and fix issues to keep everything running smoothly.\n• Bring fresh ideas to the table, challenge norms, and explore solutions through rapid prototyping.\n• Share your knowledge, inspire your team, and help elevate the organization’s problem-solving game.\n\nJob requirements:\n• Backend Enthusiast: Solid experience in backend development with C# and a passion for solving complex, technical challenges.\n• Pipeline Pro: Experience with 3D production pipelines or a strong willingness to learn the nuances of working with 3D assets and render pipelines.\n• Cloud Native: Familiarity with containerization (Docker), orchestration (Kubernetes), and cloud platforms like GCP.\n• Team Player: Excited to collaborate in a cross-functional team, sharing ideas and building tools that power great products.\n• Problem Solver: A knack for debugging, optimizing, and improving large-scale systems.\n• Bonus Points: Experience with V-Ray, 3ds Max, or AI-driven image generation.\n\nWhy Chaos?\n• A chance to work with an international team of very smart people who are passionate about changing the world.\n• An aggressively growing global product company working with the largest retailers and brands in the world.\n• Competitive compensation with benefits, and a great company culture.\n• Working for a globally recognized 3D software company known for its cutting-edge products and honored with Emmy® and Academy Awards® for its contributions to television and film.\n• Working alongside talented people in an international and diverse environment which fosters learning and knowledge-sharing.\n• Flexible working hours and work-from-home options.\n• Technical trainings and certifications.\n\nWe welcome people who value teamwork, stick to their commitments and are curious to explore new ways for achieving mastery. If you believe that you are a good match for the job, just send us your CV in English.\n\nOnly short-listed candidates will be contacted.\n\nConfidentiality of all applications is assured.","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"},{"job_id":"UH9ItkAdTygPwma0AAAAAA==","job_title":"Backend Software Developer","employer_name":"Spirii","job_description":"Spirii develops and provides world-class charging products and digital solutions to customers with electric vehicles. Our Digital Development department is proud to drive a listen, learn, and lead culture that allows us to constantly improve our ways of working. As a Back-end Software Developer, you will be part of one of our engineering teams working on innovative e-mobility projects helping our EV drivers and partners. You will work closely with internal and near-shore colleagues in the product development team and our external partners.\n\nYou will report to our Engineering Manager.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n• Solution architecture in a microservices-based context\n• Design, development and documentation of software components with a strong focus on scalability and security\n• Performance optimization\n• Data consistency and integrity\n• Collaborating with DevOps to ensure continuous integration and delivery\n• Drive the adoption of automatic testing\n• Ensure quality of releases and best practice coding standards\n\nWho You Are\n• Enjoy exploring innovative technologies and continuously expanding your skills\n• Ambitious on behalf of our customers, our company, and yourself - with a focus on excellent execution\n• High Standard of ownership in your work\n• Excellent communication skills and ability to interact with all levels in our organization as well as external partners/ customers\n• An enthusiasm for delivering high-quality software solutions\n• Take responsibility for how your work & behavior affect your colleagues – you actively participate not only in feature creation but in creating an open team environment\n\nQualifications\n• Bachelor''s degree in computer science, Software Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience)\n• Relevant experience with development of digital cloud-based solutions is required\n• 6+ years of professional software development experience\n\nExperience with;\n• Back-end development in Typescript or JavaScript (Node.js, Nest.Js)\n• Cloud-based microservice architecture\n• Deployment in cloud environments (AWS or similar)\n• Integration between external & internal IT systems (Rest API, gRPC, etc.)\n• Data/ load testing, and automation of unit/integration tests\n• Experience in eMobility industry is a plus (OCPP, OCPI, ISO-15118)\n\nBenefits\nIt is important for us to create a healthy, diverse, fun, and creative working environment, so besides all the basic benefits, we also focus a lot on social activities, flexible working hours and a good work life balance.\n• Flexible Work Environment: Enjoy a collaborative, inclusive, and open workplace designed to fit your needs and support work-life balance.\n• Competitive Package: A competitive salary, an 11% company pension plan, and a comprehensive benefits package.\n• Time to Recharge: Benefit from 32 paid vacation days (5 weeks + 5 extra) and paid parental leave to focus on what matters most.\n• Career Growth: Access professional development opportunities and grow your career in a high-impact, high-growth industry.\n• Stay Energized: Enjoy excellent coffee, tea, free snacks, and subsidized lunches at the office.\n• Stay Active: Use our Spirii gym and shared company car to keep moving.\n• Make an Impact: Be part of a team driving the future of sustainable energy while working on meaningful projects.\n• Two innovation days per month for YOU to choose what you work on.\n\nThe position is a permanent position in Copenhagen, Denmark. Danish language is not a requirement, but Fluent English language skills are required.\n\nAbout Spirii – Who We Are\nSpirii is a full-service e-Mobility provider, which offers hardware and software charging solutions to companies in the private and the public sector. Spirii has recently celebrated its four-year anniversary as a founded company, however the people in Spirii have extensive experience working with electric cars and charging, as well as development of future transport- and energy systems.\n\nSpirii is an equal opportunity employer. We encourage applications from candidates of all backgrounds and experiences. Spirii strives to create an inclusive and diverse workplace, and we encourage all qualified applicants to apply regardless of age, gender, race, sexual/religious orientation, or disability","job_location":"Copenhagen","job_employment_type":"Full-time"}]}', 'backend udvikler københavn');
